<br>
That being said, they do need to fix warriors aggro abilities.  Right now, there is no reason unless defensive is required to ever allow a warrior to be MT.<br>
<br>
Nerfing knights is not the answer.  Nor is the answer giving warriors even higher dps, hurting the other dps melee classes.<br>
<br>
The simplist way, in my opinion, would be to change the way taunt works for warriors only.  As it is now, a sucessful taunt gives the taunter aggro equal to the highest on the aggro list plus 1.  (ahem.  If you mash the taunt key everytime it pops, please read that last sentance again.  And again.  And again.  Until it is all you can see when you go to sleep at night.)  <br>
<br>
For a knight, a sucessful taunt is all we need.  We hit one taunt and then we can use our spells to burst ahead of who ever was getting wacked on, keeping aggro where it belongs, on the ones who can take the hits.<br>
<br>
For a warrior however, a sucessful taunt is not enough.  Without a reliable way to generate burst aggro, a warrior needs to either depend on a weapon proc or on straight DPS after the taunt to hold the aggro.  If that proc doesn't come before the next spell lands, or the next backstab hits, or the next double DW'd attack from the ranger or monk, then aggro is once again lost, and the warrior needs to start all over again.<br>
<br>
And heaven forbid taunt fails.  At least knights can try something else to pull aggro.  A warrior can only wait for that button to pop up again, and time how long the chanter can stand toe to toe with the quading nasty.<br>
<br>
How to fix it?  My suggestion is this.  Change the effect of taunt for warriors only from :<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>sucess gives aggro equal to highest on hate list plus 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
to<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>sucess gives aggro equal to highest on hate list plus 450*<br>
* if activated when already highest on hate list, there is no result.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
(Note:  The number 450 is chosen because that is what my highest terror now gives me, according to lucy.  I have no knowledge as to what the actual aggro numbers are.  But you get the idea.  Have it scale, so at level 30 it is highest on hatelist plus 200, at 40 300, and so on.)<br>
<br>
By doing it this way, taunt would still be used for what the designers intended.  Getting aggro when you do not have it.  If it added the bonus even when already on top of the hate list, it would completely change the ability.<br>
<br>
Knights would still be the kings of generating burst aggro, as far as tanks are concerned.<br>
<br>
The DPS classes would not have another class competing with them for group slots.<br>
<br>
And warriors would have a way to generate burst aggro when it is most needed.  In the beginning of the fight before aggro is established, or right after losing aggro.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
