<br>
However, for those who hunt often in LDoN, they should realize that aggro control there is a whole nother animal. The MOBs have few hps but high aggro modifiers against casters. Pallys and SKs are definitely the preferred tanks there (sry, warrs, u need a fix). Warrs really have to concentrate hard on those high aggro skilz early in a fite and still gotta be prepared to lose it. If the casters hold back long enough for warr to get proper aggro, your kill rate will decrease significantly. That shammy or nuker will get aggro, but usually the warr can get it rite back after the MOB gets in a few hits on the caster. That 1 extra nuke for 2k damage is almost always worth the 500 damage u take as a caster (just always have regen up). It's all about kill rate with LDoN timer. I can attest that there's like a 35 minute difference for me on adventures where the group decided to hold back or to go all out. After the last one (too close a call at 3 minutes left), I've decided to just drop groups that decide the tank needs to get proper aggro b4 I start nuking. I'm fine with taking a couple hits.<br>
<br>
KEI is pretty much a requirement for LDoN. If your tank is any good, the mana spent on healing him isn't great enough to make a dent in healer mana. I've been on plenty of adventures with not even a cleric (druid healer) and he spent most of his time nuking or healing rod damage, lol (though I told him he didn't need to, but he was always like 70m+). We had a pally to tank so I went nuke happy and didn't take any real combat damage at all.<br>
<br>
What brought this all on was because of my latest experience with Effete from Ebon Storm. The guy just has no understanding for how LDoN works and gets pissed off whenever he has to move around. He still thinks it's an exp group and it is not. He also needs to hit his taunt button sometimes and remember to tell me when his DS drops (which probably contributes most to his ability to hold aggro anyway). I think a warrior has no rite to be pissed at losing aggro in LDoN where you're killing things in seconds, not minutes. With a slower, I (as a mage) was able to tank an add with no help and just kept nuking him till he died in one adventure. I know how to control aggro. Anyone who's hunted with me in an exp group knows this. If you're dumb enough to think LDoN groups are exp groups, you should stay out of LDoN. Until you warrs get your wanted upgrade, I suggest you look into those anger augments for your weapons for LDoN. Otherwise, prepare to have a melee round or 2 stolen.<br>
<br>
Zyphanus Durga<br>
LDoN: 20 wins 7 losses<br>
