<br>
If a warrior can't hold aggro if I, as a mage, send my pet in and remain standing for 6 seconds (count that in your head, it's long), then sit down, that warrior is either doing something wrong, lazy, ill-equipped, needs to reroll into a pally or a combination of those 4?<br>
<br>
For those of you who didn't know, sending your pet in does generate a bit of aggro and coupled with sitting down immediately, may get you aggro over warrs (though not pallies or sks of course). Debuffs like Malosinia or Mala would rarely be used for 30 second or less fightes and will definitely not take aggro away from any competent warrior.<br>
<br>
I just want to explore the defining line between a bad warrior and a bad party member.<br>
<br>
Also, is it common for warrs at 61+ to not have some AAs? I may be completely wrong on this one but I thought a warrior was one of the classes where it's better to pick up a few AAs early on. I know as a mage, it's better to just get to 65 then worry about AAs (if I was a min/maxer).<br>
